<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="76">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="76">Buenos Aires [Argentina].</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="76" type="macn">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="76">MACN.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="76">
a male syntype included in the Berg collection with a blue label with the inscription &quot;Buenos Aires,&quot; a red label with the inscription 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“TYPUS,”">&quot;TYPUS,&quot;</normalizedToken>
a white label with the inscription 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Typus”">&quot;Typus&quot;</normalizedToken>
and a red label with the inscription &quot;Lectotype ♂ 
<taxonomicName authority="Bar, 1873" authorityName="Bar" authorityYear="1873" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Palustra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Palustra azollae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azollae">Palustra azollae</taxonomicName>
Berg designated by Beccacece, Vincent &amp; Navarro.&quot; We hereby designate it as lectotype [MACN]. It is in moderate condition, missing the apical half of the right antenna (Fig. 18). We designate two paralectotypes: (1) a male with red label with the inscription 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“TYPUS,”">&quot;TYPUS,&quot;</normalizedToken>
a blue label with the inscription &quot;Buenos Aires&quot; and a white label &quot;azollae Berg&quot; (handwritten by Berg), which is in quite good condition; (2) a female specimen with a blue label with the inscription &quot;Buenos Aires,&quot; a red label with the inscription 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“TYPUS”">&quot;TYPUS&quot;</normalizedToken>
and a white label with the inscription 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Typus.”">&quot;Typus.&quot;</normalizedToken>
It is in moderate to poor condition, missing the right forewing and the right hindwing is damaged.
</paragraph>
